               <head>Josh-i Faiz</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Jūsh-i fayz̤ by Sayyid Bahādur ʿAlī "Sayyid"</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100074 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85104368" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4029-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7526">Sayyid Bahādur ʿAlī "Sayyid"</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="person_f7526">سيّد بهادر على سيّد</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21957">Jūsh-i fayz̤</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21957">جوش فيض</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Rare collection of private letters, some of historical and political interest, from Farrukhabad, Lucknow, and Delhi, by the early-nineteenth-century author, <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7526" ref="Persian_0079" role="aut">Sayyid Bahādur ʿAlī mutakhalluṣ ba-Sayyid</persName>, resident of <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">qaṣbah</term>
                           <sic>Chhīrāmaʾū</sic>/<corr>
                              <name type="place">Chhibramau</name>
                           </corr>, in <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">sarkār</term>
                           <name key="http://lccn.loc.gov/n2009215599" type="place">Qannawj</name>
                        </p>
                        <p>The chronogrammatic title <q>Jūsh-i fayz̤ </q>also suggests the date of completion, <date calendar="Hijri-qamari">1249</date>/<date calendar="Gregorian">1833-4</date>
                        </p>
                        <p>The work consists of a short preface followed by 140 letters in total, some of which relate to exchanges with and observations on European officers, while others mention the affairs of women in varied professions and social circumstances</p>
                        <p>No filiation details provided</p>
                        <p>Not dated</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>Copied from an original =-=-=-=-</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
